                    <p>The more one becomes educated on Bitcoin and the history of our federal reserve financial ponzi scam system, the more you lean towards the side of Bitcoin. The powers that be are very against Bitcoin. This is good news. This means they are NOT in control of Bitcoin in any way, shape or form. If they were, they wouldn&#8217;t be so against it and would probably even promote it. </p>
<p>Now that we know they are not controlling it, people have a choice. They can side with the scam system that has been raping them for 100 years OR they can side with Bitcoin or another alt-digital currency. It&#8217;s that simple.  Things in life can be very simple if you do not act from a place of fear AND you can think clearly.</p>
<p>We know that some sheeple will side with the powers  that have been continuously raping them every day. They are conditioned little sheeple and we can&#8217;t do much about them. Can&#8217;t fix stupid. They are fully enslaved. But the rest of us that are thinking, living, breathing conscious souls, who choose to use their free will, can and should do something about it. </p>
<p>As one of these people that ARE awake, I have no interest in discussions regarding blending with the current financial scam system. No interest in cooperating with the scam banking system. No interest in regulation, taxation or any of the BS issues these criminals like to talk about so they can start to take over and suppress the free will of the people.</p>
<p>The discussion should NOT be about all of these BS issues so the powers that be can get in at every possible juncture and get their piece of extorted flesh. The discussions should ONLY be about how to get rid of them sticking their nose in other people&#8217;s business. That&#8217;s the only discussion that should be talked about. So when they convene a meeting regarding regulation or licensing of Bitcoin or some other BS power grab, every single comment,  voice or letter written should have nothing to do with that line of thought process and all questions should be on them to explain why they should have their hand in anything. </p>
<p>Get the concept? Now get to it.</p>
